I'd concentrate on INT and MANA items first, and CHA only if you plan on doing a lot of charming.

A horse/drogmor is a great investment, too, but I wouldn't get anything higher than the cheapest.  

And if you really want to splurge for a toy with no real practical use, get Perserved Chokidai Vocal Cords.  They have a clicky-effect of Voice Graft and are enchanter-equipable.  (Can't wait till I get Dire Charm!  Only 7 more AA.)

I like my ench, who is 65 with about 28 AA (Run3, Metabolism3 (for sitting on my hungry horse), MGB, etc).  I recently joined a raiding guild, where my tasks are pretty much limited to buffing before we start.  We have shaman to slow.  I'll Tash, and occassionally have a chance to mez, but other than that it's Cripple and Nuke (Insanity, 1100 points).

I didn't solo much, but when I did it was with my summoned pet, not a charmed mob.  I hear chanters can charm-solo well in HoH, but I haven't tried it yet (too scared).

Good luck, and enjoy!
-- C.

